To start a new project 
------------------------

At the command line enter
1. npm init - to create the package.json file and follow the steps to enter all its properties
2. npm install <packagename> - to install a package and save it as a dependency in the package.json file and also to create the package-lock.json file
3. Install nodemon to watch for changes to files and automatically update server.  From the command lin enter npm install -g nodemon
4. Create a server.js file and copy template code into this file (see online examples). Then at the command line enter node server.js to start the server
Open the browser and go to the local host name to view the app on the local server
